<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="522" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,942,2013]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1086,1112]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,430,1086,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[329,430,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. zhengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[438,529,1086,1112]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[438,529,1086,1112]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ye, Polhemus &amp; Bu, 2013" authorityName="Ye, Polhemus &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2013" box="[678,1143,1086,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">
<emphasis box="[678,838,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. taiwanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ye, Z. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. &amp; Bu, W. J." box="[847,1143,1086,1113]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" pagination="290 - 318" refId="ref7712" refString="Ye, Z., Polhemus, D. A. &amp; Bu, W. J. (2013) A taxonomic contribution to the genus Pseudovelia Hoberlandt, 1951 (Hemiptera: Veliidae) from China, with descriptions of ten new species. Zootaxa, 3636 (2), 290 - 318. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3636.2.4" type="journal article" year="2013">Ye, Polhemus &amp; Bu, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ye &amp; Bu, 2015" authorityName="Ye &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[1199,1370,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. sichuanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ye, Z. &amp; Bu, W. J." pageId="15" pageNumber="522" pagination="183 - 191" refId="ref7781" refString="Ye, Z. &amp; Bu, W. J. (2015) Three new species of the genus Pseudovelia Hoberlandt, 1950 (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Veliidae) from China. Zootaxa, 4039 (1), 183 - 191. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4039.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Ye &amp; Bu, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye" authorityYear="2022" box="[389,491,1122,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[389,491,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. zhengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[500,591,1122,1148]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[500,591,1122,1148]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ye, Polhemus &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2013" box="[904,1066,1123,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">
<emphasis box="[904,1066,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. taiwanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its relatively longer body (
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. zhengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[231,321,1158,1184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[231,321,1158,1184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
2.26–2.31 vs. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ye, Polhemus &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2013" box="[486,645,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">
<emphasis box="[486,645,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. taiwanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
2.05–2.09) and more slender abdominal segment VIII (i.e., about 2.31 times as long as wide, 
<figureCitation box="[405,498,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[174,1415,226,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[151,1436,211,1681]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 35. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 36. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 37. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 38. P. plauta sp. nov.; 39. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 40. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816737" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816737/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Figs. 40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[509,540,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1813,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,216,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[151,1436,211,1738]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 41. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 42. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 43. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 44. P. plauta sp. nov.; 45. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 46. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816739/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">46</figureCitation>
), whereas abdominal segment VIII of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ye, Polhemus &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2013" box="[970,1130,1195,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">
<emphasis box="[970,1130,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. taiwanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is about 1.96 times as long as wide. In addition, compared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ye, Polhemus &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2013" box="[556,715,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">
<emphasis box="[556,715,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. taiwanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the medial portion on the venter of the fore tibia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye" authorityYear="2022" box="[1297,1396,1230,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1297,1396,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. zhengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="15" pageNumber="522" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a distinct process. This species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ye &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2015" box="[895,1065,1266,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[895,1065,1266,1292]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the hind margin of abdominal segment VIII without some distinct specific modifications (e.g., distinct laminar processes) (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1294,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[174,1415,226,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[151,1436,211,1681]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 35. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 36. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 37. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 38. P. plauta sp. nov.; 39. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 40. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816737" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816737/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Figs. 40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1306,1337,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1813,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,216,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[151,1436,211,1738]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 41. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 42. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 43. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 44. P. plauta sp. nov.; 45. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 46. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816739/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">46</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1349,1379,1302,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[173,1410,201,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,181,1808]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 47. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 48. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 49. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 50. P. plauta sp. nov.; 51. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 52. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816743/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">52</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1392,1424,1302,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–58" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,182,1778]" captionTargetId="figure-21@12.[151,1436,181,1795]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 53–58. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 53. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 54. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 55. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 56. P. plauta sp. nov.; 57. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 58. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816745/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">58</figureCitation>
). Moreover, the abdomen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye" authorityYear="2022" box="[459,561,1338,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[459,561,1338,1364]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. zhengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[569,659,1338,1364]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[569,659,1338,1364]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is more slender than the abdomen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ye &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2015" box="[1088,1259,1338,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[1088,1259,1338,1364]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the end of the abdomen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Jin &amp; Bu &amp; Ye" authorityYear="2022" box="[332,433,1374,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[332,433,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. zhengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[440,529,1374,1400]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[440,529,1374,1400]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
does not have dense, short hairs compared to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ye &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2015" box="[1125,1296,1374,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[1125,1296,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">P. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="523" pageId="15" pageNumber="522" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,942,2013]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,150,1041]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="523" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,526,1410,1436]" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Description. Apterous male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[541,610,1410,1436]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1330,191,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[241,1345,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Habitus of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 1. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 2. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 3. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 4. P. plauta sp. nov.; 5. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 6. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816717/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Color: ground color yellowish-brown, head brown, clypeus brown, rostrum yellowish-brown with black apex, buccula red-brown; antennal segment I yellowish-brown, apical part infuscated, segments II–IV brown; pronotum yellowish-brown, with dense black spots on posterior part, lateral part of metanotum yellowish-brown; legs (
<figureCitation box="[552,647,1518,1544]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1173,1197]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,193,1138]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[151,1436,181,1149]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Fore legs of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 17. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 18. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 19. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 20. P. plauta sp. nov.; 21. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 22. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816727/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Figs. 22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[659,689,1518,1544]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–28" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[163,1426,1001,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-396@7.[152,1436,993,1881]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–28. Middle legs of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 23. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 24. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 25. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 26. P. plauta sp. nov.; 27. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 28. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">28</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[702,731,1518,1544]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1043,1067]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,189,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[151,1436,181,1019]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Hind legs of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 29. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 30. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 31. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 32. P. plauta sp. nov.; 33. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 34. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816733/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">34</figureCitation>
) mainly yellowish-brown, femora yellowish, apices of femora infuscated, tibiae and tarsi brown, grasping combs brown; mediotergites dark-brown, connexiva yellowish-brown, lateral part of mediotergite I, medial parts of mediotergites II, III, VI and VII with prominent silvery pubescence; abdominal segment VIII (
<figureCitation box="[444,540,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[174,1415,226,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[151,1436,211,1681]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 35. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 36. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 37. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 38. P. plauta sp. nov.; 39. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 40. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816737" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816737/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Figs. 40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[553,584,1626,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[173,1410,201,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,181,1808]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 47. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 48. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 49. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 50. P. plauta sp. nov.; 51. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 52. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816743/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">52</figureCitation>
), pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[742,825,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–64" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1165,1189]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,196,1128]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[205,1381,181,1141]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59–64. Pygophore of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 59. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 60. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 61. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 62. P. plauta sp. nov.; 63. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 64. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816747/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
) and proctiger yellowish, each of them weakly infuscated apically. Structural characteristics: body small-sized, bearing short and grayish setae, area around eyes and antennal segment I covered by relatively few, longer, grayish setae. Head short and wide, relatively perpendicular to thorax, without inflection; buccula clearly visible, but not produced posteriorly; eyes bare except for the presence of two ocular setae. Pronotum relatively broad, bearing dense, dark punctures on the posterior portion of lobe, hind pronotal margin nearly straight, anterior margin slightly emarginated; metanotum completely hidden beneath pronotal lobe except laterally. Fore tibia (
<figureCitation box="[609,690,1842,1868]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1173,1197]" captionTargetBox="[159,1414,193,1138]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[151,1436,181,1149]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Fore legs of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 17. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 18. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 19. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 20. P. plauta sp. nov.; 21. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 22. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816727/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) covered with dense, short setae, medial part of venter on fore tibia with process, grasping comb relatively thin; middle leg (
<figureCitation box="[777,858,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–28" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[163,1426,1001,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-396@7.[152,1436,993,1881]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–28. Middle legs of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 23. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 24. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 25. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 26. P. plauta sp. nov.; 27. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 28. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816731/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) slender, tibia covered with dense, suberect, slender setae; hind femur (
<figureCitation box="[365,447,1914,1940]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1043,1067]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,189,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[151,1436,181,1019]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Hind legs of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 29. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 30. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 31. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 32. P. plauta sp. nov.; 33. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 34. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816733/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) slightly stout, tibia with suberect, needle-like setae, basal part of venter on hind tarsal segment I with a tuft of long, black bristles (
<figureCitation box="[651,735,1950,1976]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1043,1067]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,189,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[151,1436,181,1019]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Hind legs of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 29. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 30. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 31. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 32. P. plauta sp. nov.; 33. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 34. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816733/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="522">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
), ventral arolium bristle-like. Abdomen almost flat, connexiva slightly raised, with suberect, few, short and brown setae; abdominal venter flat. Genital segments: relatively small, abdominal segment VIII (
<figureCitation box="[447,544,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[174,1415,226,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[151,1436,211,1681]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 35. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 36. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 37. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 38. P. plauta sp. nov.; 39. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 40. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816737" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816737/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">Figs. 40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[557,588,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1813,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,216,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[151,1436,211,1738]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 41. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 42. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 43. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 44. P. plauta sp. nov.; 45. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 46. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816739/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">46</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[601,631,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[173,1410,201,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,181,1808]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 47. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 48. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 49. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 50. P. plauta sp. nov.; 51. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 52. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816743/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">52</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[646,675,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–58" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,182,1778]" captionTargetId="figure-21@12.[151,1436,181,1795]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 53–58. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 53. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 54. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 55. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 56. P. plauta sp. nov.; 57. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 58. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816745/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">58</figureCitation>
) relatively slender, tubular-like, about 2.31 times as long as wide, hind margin with dense, short and brown hairs, ventrally with subtriangular depression, lateral margins of depression with a pair of short, brown setae, hind margin of depression with a pair of tiny processes with tufts of short, brown setae; lateral margin of pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[630,712,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–64" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1165,1189]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,196,1128]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[205,1381,181,1141]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59–64. Pygophore of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 59. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 60. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 61. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 62. P. plauta sp. nov.; 63. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 64. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816747/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
) with a pair of yellowish hairs, posterior part of pygophore with dense, yellowish hairs; proctiger subrectangular, with rounded apex; parameres symmetrical, small, stick-like, with rounded apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,397,366,392]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">Apterous female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[415,501,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[271,1323,194,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[254,1333,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Habitus of Pseudovelia spp. (apterous females). 7. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 8. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 9. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 10. P. plauta sp. nov.; 11. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 12. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816721/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Color: similar to male. Structural characteristics: body medium-sized, relatively stout, slightly larger than males, structure of head including antenna as in male; fore tibia without grasping comb, hind tibia and tarsus not modified, venter of hind tarsal segment I without a tuft of bristles; abdomen pleurally and ventrally without special modifications, connexiva relatively broad, slightly raised, converging posteriorly and touching caudally; gonocaxa I elongate, proctiger yellowish-brown, with dense, short, brown setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,1041]" box="[199,871,546,573]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,752,546,573]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">Macropterous female and macropterous male:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,568,582,609]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">Measurements. Apterous male.</emphasis>
Body length: 2.26–2.31 (
<typeStatus box="[855,960,583,609]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">holotype</typeStatus>
:2.28), head width: 0.50–0.53, head length: 0.30–0.33, head width about 1.75 times head length; antenna about 0.57 times as long as body, length of antennal segments I–IV: 0.40, 0.26, 0.28 and 0.38; pronotum width: 0.67–0.71, pronotum length: 0.38–0.40, about 1.75 times as wide as long; length of grasping comb 0.30, about 0.54 times tibial length; length of leg segments (femur, tibia and tarsus): fore leg: 0.61, 0.56 and 0.30, middle leg: 0.78, 0.71 and 0.42 (0.14+0.28), hind leg: 0.89, 0.88 and 0.55 (0.26+0.29). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[297,500,762,788]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">Apterous female.</emphasis>
Body length: 2.48–2.51, head width: 0.53–0.56, head length: 0.32–0.35, head width about 1.62 times head length, antenna about 0.54 times as long as body, length of antennal segments I–IV: 0.41, 0.27, 0.29, 0.39; pronotum width: 0.73–0.78, pronotum length: 0.38–0.41, about 1.88 times as wide as long; length of leg segments (femur, tibia and tarsus): fore leg: 0.60, 0.57 and 0.31, middle leg: 0.79, 0.72 and 0.43 (0.14+0.29), hind leg: 0.89, 0.87 and 0.54 (0.20+0.34);
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="523" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,943,969]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named in honour of Prof. Leyi Zheng for his outstanding contributions to the study of the Chinese fauna of 
<taxonomicName box="[419,555,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="523" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heteroptera</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
